{"ts":"2026-05-22T19:30:32.503Z","author":"codex-plan-worker-20260522","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments/1","value":{"created_at":"2026-05-22T19:30:32.503Z","author":"codex-plan-worker-20260522","text":"Evidence: implemented pm plan materialize and text alias fixes.\n\nBehavior changed: --steps all now materializes every plan step; materialize no longer adds reverse top-level child dependencies from the Plan to generated items, preserving step-level implements links and avoiding lifecycle dependency cycles; decision/discovery/validation now accept shorthand option keys for MCP/programmatic calls plus CLI flags --decision/--discovery/--validation, with plan contracts advertising those aliases.\n\nVerification: npm install -g . (up to date); pm --version 2026.5.18; node -v v25.9.0; pnpm -v 10.33.0; pnpm build passed; pm test --run passed for node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts (17 tests) and tests/unit/plan-command.spec.ts (24 tests); direct CLI probe pm plan decision <id> --decision \"pick alias\" --json exited 0; node dist/cli.js contracts --command plan --flags-only --json shows --decision/--discovery/--validation aliases; git diff --check passed.\n\nNote: CLI shorthand support required narrow parser/contract edits in src/cli/register-mutation.ts and src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts because Commander rejected --decision before src/cli/commands/plan.ts could run.\n"}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-05-22T19:30:32.503Z"}],"before_hash":"0b283c2ed992ed9038ae5411fbbfb64a3bceebf45eef744796fd8e024cc8f3aa","after_hash":"8a09d4c6bcf365ae072e2bf43a12f5fc81cdb9f896509b957bb288aaf3cef9bc"}
